Mastering JavaScript Fundamentals

This project demonstrates the fundamentals of JavaScript including variables, conditionals, functions, loops, and DOM manipulation. The goal is to show how JavaScript can make static web pages interactive and dynamic.

📂 Project Structure
📁 project-folder
 ┣ 📄 index.html   → HTML structure
 ┣ 📄 style.css    → Styling 
 ┗ 📄 script.js    → JavaScript logic

🚀 Features
✅ Part 1: JavaScript Basics
Prompts the user for their age and displays whether they are an adult or minor.
Demonstrates variable declaration, type conversion, and if/else conditionals.


✅ Part 2: Functions
Calculate Total: Adds two numbers entered in input fields and displays the result.
Toggle Message: Shows or hides a message on the page when a button is clicked.


✅ Part 3: Loops
For Loop Example: Generates a list of numbers from 1 to 5 dynamically.
While Loop Example: Creates a countdown from 5 to 1.


✅ Part 4: DOM Manipulation
Change Button Colors: Changes all buttons from blue to light purple with one click.
Dynamic List (Alphabet Generator): Adds alphabets sequentially (A → B → ... → Z) each time the button is clicked.
Footer Color Toggle: Changes the footer background color when clicked.


🎯 Learning Outcomes
Clear understanding of variables, conditionals, functions, and loops.
Hands-on practice with DOM methods like getElementById, querySelector, appendChild.
Responsive interactivity using event listeners.
Clean, well-commented JavaScript code following best practices.


🛠️ How to Run
Download or clone this repository.
Open index.html in your web browser.
Interact with the buttons to see JavaScript in action 🎉.